 IMHO, the simple feature in place today may be OK for a small number of watch items, but doesn't work very well when collaborating with a larger number people across a larger number of topics.  Feedback I've heard from other folks is that many don't use the workbox. Nevertheless, I think it could be a valuable core component of Confluence life if we could move items from the workbox to a virtual donebox or just hide them at the user's discretion.

I get many notices on important things that I watch, but there is no way to tick them off and mark them processed.  I watch these spaces because I collaborate to do work, not just to see a log of what was touched. Can we make this more of an actual work box?

Apologies if I missed a previous similar suggestion.

