We would like to have a gadget to allow voting against features suggested through Confluence. Much in the same way as the Vote feature in JIRA.

As of 5.10, it's no longer possible to trigger read-only mode with an expired evaluation license or by exceeding the user count on a license, as described in this KB article: [How to Make Confluence Read-Only|https://confluence.atlassian.com/confkb/how-to-make-confluence-read-only-311920317.html].

h3. Steps to reproduce
# Apply an expired evaluation license, or a 10-user license with 13 users
# Create or edit a page

h3. Expected results

You will be unable to create or edit a page, and a message like the following would be displayed: [^read-only.png]

h3. Actual results

You can successfully create and edit a page

h3. Relevant code

The following are the methods and relevant sections of code, from {{ConfluenceWorkflowInterceptor.java}}:

{code}
public String intercept(ActionInvocation actionInvocation) throws Exception {
        if (actionInvocation.getAction() instanceof ConfluenceActionSupport) {
            if (shouldCheckForLicense(actionInvocation)) {
                if (GeneralUtil.isLicenseExpired())
                    return ConfluenceActionSupport.LICENSE_EXPIRED;

                // If there are too many users for the current license...
                if (getUserChecker() != null && getUserChecker().hasTooManyUsers())
                    return ConfluenceActionSupport.LICENSE_USERS_EXCEEDED;
            }
        }

private boolean shouldCheckForLicense(ActionInvocation actionInvocation) {
        return BootstrapUtils.getBootstrapManager().isSetupComplete() &&
                (actionInvocation.getAction() instanceof CreateSpaceAction) ||
                (actionInvocation.getAction() instanceof EditSpaceAction) ||
                (actionInvocation.getAction() instanceof CreatePageAction) ||
                (actionInvocation.getAction() instanceof EditPageAction) ||
                (actionInvocation.getAction() instanceof CreateBlogPostAction) ||
                (actionInvocation.getAction() instanceof EditBlogPostAction);
    }
{code}

For whatever reason, "CreatePageAction" and "EditPageAction" don't fire anymore, when creating or editing a page.

I've marked this as critical because of the potential impact it can have on our bottom line if customers discover this behavior.

