I've turned on the beta version of our On Demand instance and am very disappointed and concerned. No longer having the default behavior of the compact page tree in the left sidebar is conflicts with how we use the system. We rely on that feature to be a table of contents and immediate guide to a space so that users know at a glance what content is available. We also have written many tutorials and specifications that use that left side page tree as the only source of navigation.

The multi step process to get a page tree back is not a good option, plus it takes up much more screen real estate than before. We are very unhappy with this change and hope the beta program provides opportunity for this feedback to be heard. I consider the system to be significantly less usable if this feature stays.

I'm also unable to find any release notes for this beta so can not determine if there is any support for disabling this feature, what to call it or how to submit beta feedback.

